The paper focuses on using Process Mining to extract insights from smart home environments, which is a topic related to Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses supervised learning techniques to train the abstraction framework, which falls under Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper deals with data analysis and interpretation, which is related to Cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of precision and F-score to evaluate the performance of the abstraction framework, which is related to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
